    "selector": "Witdrawal",
    "selector_info": "Selecting \"Yes\" indicates that ASM withdrawal was performed after a seizure-free period of at least two years. Withdrawal in this study involved a gradual tapering process, typically lasting six months or longer, to minimize risks. In the withdrawal group, 264 patients were analyzed. Other risk factors should be kept in mind: patients with a shorter seizure-free period (<4 years), a longer history of active epilepsy, or those who underwent rapid tapering faced significantly higher risks of seizure recurrence.",
